"""
frb_mcmc_v4_fixed.py
========================================================
Bayesian MCMC analysis of FRB 20180916B broadband constraints
Campaign: SRT_11-24 (PI: A. Anandhu) + September 2023 MWL campaign

Three analysis modules
  1.  Spectral index fitting  – radio SED (detections + upper limits)
  2.  Synchrotron-shock model – parameter constraints from optical + X-ray ULs
  3.  Magnetospheric efficiency – eta_X and eta_opt posterior upper bounds

Sampler: Metropolis-Hastings, 300 000 steps, 40 % burn-in, thinning = 25

References
----------
Bethapudi et al. (2022, 2023) -- Effelsberg detections
Pilia et al. (2020)           -- SRT P-band detections
Trudu et al. (2023)           -- uGMRT B3 detections
Pleunis et al. (2021)         -- LOFAR detections
Gopinath et al. (2024)        -- LOFAR detections
CHIME/FRB Collaboration (2019, 2020) -- CHIME detections
Kilpatrick et al. (2023)      -- Gemini optical upper limit
Scholz et al. (2020)          -- Chandra / Fermi upper limits
Metzger et al. (2019)         -- External-shock model scalings
Beloborodov (2020)            -- Shock synchrotron fluence calibration
Mereghetti et al. (2020)      -- SGR 1935+2154 X-ray event
"""

